{"slug": "replication_crisis", "name": "The Replication Crisis", "commander": "Satya, Aetherflux Genius", "colors": "Jeskai", "pips": ["W", "U", "R"], "archetype": "Copy / clone", "status": "Elite", "bracket": 3, "score": 17, "axes": [{"label": "Core loop", "score": 5}, {"label": "Kill reliability", "score": 4}, {"label": "Durability", "score": 4}, {"label": "Interaction", "score": 4}], "gc": ["Cyclonic Rift", "Fierce Guardianship", "The One Ring"], "clock": {"decap": "T7", "table": "T10", "grid": [3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 10, 12], "decapCurve": [0, 0, 4, 18, 59, 80, 94, 99], "tableCurve": [0, 0, 2, 5, 9, 13, 41, 80], "never": [1, 20], "src": "lab rc_speed_lab @8k (ALL-IN ceiling; SQUAD defended proxy ~1 turn slower)"}, "gamePlan": "Satya's \"whenever attacks\" trigger creates a free token copy of any nontoken creature you control, plus 2 free energy. The deck stacks ETB creatures for Satya to repeatedly copy, with token doublers and a real combat-loop kill line.", "winLine": "Satya + Sword of F&F + Aggravated Assault -> infinite combats", "finishers": [{"name": "Satya + Lightning Runner (infinite combats, 2 cards = commander + 1) \u2014 PRIMARY", "tag": "added 2026-06-22", "note": ""}, {"name": "Sword of F&F + Aggravated Assault (infinite combats, 3 cards including commander)", "tag": "backup infinite", "note": ""}, {"name": "Brudiclad Token Conversion", "tag": "alpha strike, no infinite required", "note": ""}, {"name": "Adeline + Anointed Procession Token Flood", "tag": "", "note": ""}, {"name": "Zealous Conscripts Steal", "tag": "", "note": ""}, {"name": "Value Grind", "tag": "", "note": ""}], "rulings": [{"name": "Tokens entering \"tapped and attacking\" do NOT trigger \"whenever ~ attacks\" abilities", "note": "the combat they're made \u2014 but they CAN attack normally in a later combat (once untapped + declared), and then they trigger. Satya copies of Adeline, Phelia, Bident-bearers, etc. don't fire attack triggers on entry, but their ETB triggers DO. This is the whole engine of the Lightning Runner combo: the token Runner makes no energy the combat Satya creates it, but it untaps with the others and does make energy when it attacks in the next combat. (It's also why the old Combat Celebrant \"infinite\" was fake \u2014 exert is a one-time, can't-untap thing.)"}, {"name": "The copy must target a nontoken creature", "note": "Brudiclad-converted tokens are not legal Satya targets."}, {"name": "Energy is gained free; tokens are kept by paying their mana value in {E} at end step.", "note": "An Inferno Titan token costs 6{E} to keep \u2014 three attacks bank enough for one. Unkept tokens are sacrificed."}, {"name": "Brudiclad-converted tokens shed Satya's end-of-turn sacrifice clause", "note": "(it's a delayed trigger stuck to the original token) \u2014 the cleanest way to keep tokens without paying energy."}, {"name": "The Sword + AA loop relies on Satya herself connecting", "note": "not the tokens. Menace + haste + 5 toughness makes it reliable, but two blockers stop menace."}, {"name": "Panharmonicon / Elesh Norn double the ETBs of every Satya copy", "note": "Strionic Resonator copies Satya's attack trigger for a second token. Phelia and Restoration Angel are the flicker engines (Phelia only flickers when she attacks)."}], "composition": [{"name": "Game Changers", "count": 3}, {"name": "ETB Creatures \u2014 Value", "count": 5}, {"name": "ETB Creatures \u2014 Board Impact", "count": 6}, {"name": "ETB Creatures \u2014 Tokens/Pump", "count": 4}, {"name": "ETB Creatures \u2014 Utility", "count": 1}, {"name": "Combat Engine / Infinite Combo Pieces", "count": 2}, {"name": "ETB Doublers / Token Multipliers", "count": 5}, {"name": "Token Conversion", "count": 1}, {"name": "Combat Value Creatures", "count": 1}, {"name": "Tutors", "count": 1}, {"name": "Stax / Draw", "count": 2}, {"name": "Counterspells", "count": 3}, {"name": "Removal", "count": 6}, {"name": "Flexible Removal", "count": 2}, {"name": "Flexible Interaction", "count": 3}, {